newsitem.title: USA: U.S. Spring/White Wheat-Bids mixed, sales slacken.
newsitem.headline: U.S. Spring/White Wheat-Bids mixed, sales slacken.

text.p: Dark northern spring wheat cash bids were mixed on Monday in subdued dealings, dealers said.
December MGE spring wheat futures gained 1-1/2 cent to end at $4.30-3/4 a bushel.
Movement was very slow. "It was an extremely quiet day," a Minneapolis dealer said. Farmers are still waiting for higher prices. But it does not look like they will get that for quite a while."
An Oregon dealer concurred that activity was lackluster. "We are waiting for export activity," he said.
